data.description:
Location...Location...Location.  

Imagine waking up in the serene town of Brandenburg, minutes from Fort Knox, KY, surrounded by the beauty of nature and the charm of a gated community. As you step into your KSK Construction Single Family Ranch style home, the open floor plan welcomes you with elegance and warmth. The custom cabinets and granite countertops throughout the house add a touch of luxury to your daily life. The oversized two car garage (24x29) will fit a 3/4 Ton 4WD Pickup Truck easily with room to spare. 

Picture yourself in the spacious kitchen, whipping up delightful meals on the large kitchen island, while the adjacent formal dining area and living room create the perfect space for family gatherings and entertaining friends. The bedrooms, adorned with blackout shades for peaceful nights, offer comfort and privacy.

And let's not forget the basement—a haven with 9' ceilings, a generous fourth bedroom, and a full bathroom. The storage room, complete with built-in shelving, adds a practical touch to keep your space organized effortlessly. This home also features a Puronics Whole House Water Softener and Reverse Osmosis drinking water system. Never buy bottled water again!

Step outside onto the expansive deck overlooking the shaded backyard, where tranquility meets adventure with the adjacent golf course. This home is perfectly placed between the 16th and 17th holes.  

Beyond the walls of your dream home, the gated community of Doe Valley unfolds with guarded entrances, a private lake, boat rentals, tennis courts, basketball courts, a weekly farmer's market, a private club, and a community pool. It's not just a house; it's a lifestyle—a place where every day feels like a vacation. Oh, and the neighbors are super friendly. Brought us a bottle of bourbon the day we moved in!

Brandenburg is a small community with friendly people. The local sports are fantastic and the public schools are highly rated.  This house is about 30 minutes from Louisville International Airport. 

And to top it off, the thoughtful military family who's been taking care of your home ensures it remains in impeccable condition. Summer 2024 marks the beginning of a new chapter for someone fortunate enough to call this place home. It's not just a move; it's an upgrade to a life of comfort, luxury, and community.
